Milena Gardosh.

1050
01:37:32,264 --> 01:37:37,394
<i>It was almost midnight by the time
Dr. Green got to Hampstead.</i>

1051
01:37:53,744 --> 01:37:54,744
What is it?

1052
01:37:54,912 --> 01:37:57,831
Thank God.
Listen, we don't have much time.

1053
01:37:58,082 --> 01:38:00,793
You're in danger.
She's going to try and kill you.

1054
01:38:01,001 --> 01:38:03,087
What? Who's trying to kill me?

1055
01:38:03,546 --> 01:38:04,672
Catherine.

1056
01:38:09,051 --> 01:38:11,512
I thought I could help her
but I was wrong.

1057
01:38:11,762 --> 01:38:15,474
I'll try and get her sectioned.
It's the only thing that'll stop her.

1058
01:38:16,725 --> 01:38:18,769
I've already spoken to Catherine.

1059
01:38:22,940 --> 01:38:25,609
She's very upset. You terrified her.

1060
01:38:27,194 --> 01:38:31,282
I terrified her? She's a murderer.
She's already admitted it.

1061
01:38:31,532 --> 01:38:34,159
Fr r

1062
01:38:34,410 --> 01:38:36,662
You assaulted her.
She nearly drowned.

1063
01:38:38,914 --> 01:38:42,876
You've broken the law, not to mention
the ethical canon of our profession.

1064
01:38:43,168 --> 01:38:44,169
It wasn't like that.

1065
01:38:44,420 --> 01:38:46,505
Michael, listen to me, please.

1066
01:38:46,755 --> 01:38:48,549
You're not well.

1067
01:38:49,842 --> 01:38:51,552
You're the one who needs help.

1068
01:38:56,140 --> 01:38:57,891
...

1069
01:38:58,142 --> 01:39:02,730
and he thinks that if you volunteer
for a 28-day observation...

1070
01:39:02,938 --> 01:39:05,899
you might be able to avoid
criminal charges.

1071
01:39:07,192 --> 01:39:11,655
However, they will have to
revoke your license.

1072
01:39:12,740 --> 01:39:13,741
I'm sorry.

1073
01:39:14,908 --> 01:39:16,243
She's right.

1074
01:39:16,744 --> 01:39:19,204
It's for your own good, Michael.

1075
01:39:24,752 --> 01:39:27,379
She asked me
to take over her treatment.

1076
01:39:28,797 --> 01:39:30,716
She's my patient now.

1077
01:39:33,177 --> 01:39:34,511
Please, don't.

1078
01:39:38,390 --> 01:39:40,809
You've no idea what
you're getting into.

1079
01:39:42,645 --> 01:39:44,021
Tell her the truth.

1080
01:39:46,649 --> 01:39:48,025
Tell her the truth.

1081
01:39:50,235 --> 01:39:51,654
I'll make you tell her the truth.

1082
01:39:57,284 --> 01:39:58,284
God.

1083
01:39:59,870 --> 01:40:00,870
Come on.

1084
01:40:07,503 --> 01:40:09,838
She's right, you know.

1085
01:40:10,089 --> 01:40:12,800
You really do need help.

1086
01:40:18,931 --> 01:40:19,973
Bitch.

1087
01:40:25,604 --> 01:40:27,272
So, what's this about?

1088
01:40:29,566 --> 01:40:30,693
Protection.

1089
01:40:31,151 --> 01:40:32,986
Oh, yeah? From who?

1090
01:40:35,781 --> 01:40:37,116
Washburn.

1091
01:40:41,495 --> 01:40:42,746
Go ahead.

1092
01:40:47,710 --> 01:40:51,296
Kelly Lash kills Irena,
Dr. Green's colleague.

1093
01:40:51,547 --> 01:40:53,507
No, I read your book.

1094
01:40:53,716 --> 01:40:57,344
So you just rushed right over here
to save her?

1095
01:40:57,594 --> 01:41:01,849
It's just a story, doctor.
Or maybe I really am omnipotent.

1096
01:41:04,184 --> 01:41:09,440
Congratulations,
the control freak finally lets go.

1097
01:41:09,690 --> 01:41:13,569
This is what you wanted from the start,
wasn't it? To ruin me, to fuck me up!

1098
01:41:14,903 --> 01:41:16,905
Feels good, doesn't it?

1099
01:41:19,116 --> 01:41:24,538
No more "I should've stopped Cheslav
from killing his girlfriend."

1100
01:41:24,788 --> 01:41:28,000
No more whining over nothing.

1101
01:41:28,417 --> 01:41:31,086
- It wasn't over nothing.
- Yes, it was.

1102
01:41:31,336 --> 01:41:34,423
Cheslav did not kill his girlfriend.

1103
01:41:35,549 --> 01:41:37,217
Washburn did.

1104
01:41:39,136 --> 01:41:40,304
Washburn?

1105
01:41:40,554 --> 01:41:44,516
What do you think Adam Towers was
writing about when he was killed?

1106
01:41:45,058 --> 01:41:49,313
You're lying.
You're a lying fucking bitch.

1107
01:41:49,563 --> 01:41:53,066
Sure I am,
if it makes it easier for you.

1108
01:41:54,693 --> 01:41:58,614
Why? Why would he kill
the girlfriend?

1109
01:42:01,074 --> 01:42:03,076
T nail

1110
01:42:13,962 --> 01:42:15,506
That's right.

1111
01:42:16,924 --> 01:42:18,801
Your seven years of hell.

1112
01:42:20,093 --> 01:42:21,845
Your meltdown.

1113
01:42:22,095 --> 01:42:23,764
Your divorce.

1114
01:42:25,349 --> 01:42:30,145
Just so your good friend Roy
could nail a drug dealer.

1115
01:42:40,781 --> 01:42:42,449
Don't take it so hard.

1116
01:42:42,699 --> 01:42:46,161
Even Oedipus
didn't see his mother coming.

1117
01:42:53,627 --> 01:42:55,754
It's Roy Washburn.

1118
01:42:57,673 --> 01:43:00,092
Give me the gun. Give me the gun!

1119
01:43:00,509 --> 01:43:01,760
Fuck off!

1120
01:43:02,010 --> 01:43:06,473
Give me the gun! He knows I've got
Towers' notes. He wants me dead.

1121
01:43:06,723 --> 01:43:08,600
Open the door!

1122
01:43:08,851 --> 01:43:11,270
He's going to kill me
and say you did it.

1123
01:43:11,895 --> 01:43:15,399
No. No, this is all fucked up.

1124
01:43:15,649 --> 01:43:19,695
You don't know what you're doing.
Give me the gun. He's going to kill me.

1125
01:43:19,945 --> 01:43:21,238
You...!

1126
01:43:25,284 --> 01:43:26,952
Go ahead, then, baby.

1127
01:43:43,051 --> 01:43:45,846
Whatever she told you, she's lying.

1128
01:43:48,932 --> 01:43:50,350
Kill her!

1129
01:43:50,601 --> 01:43:53,061
It's the only chance you've got.

1130
01:44:29,473 --> 01:44:31,058
Let go of the gun!

1131
01:44:31,308 --> 01:44:32,684
Clear the weapon!

1132
01:44:32,935 --> 01:44:35,228
- Stay still!
- Get off me!

1133
01:44:35,479 --> 01:44:38,023
Stop struggling! Stop struggling!

1134
01:44:38,273 --> 01:44:42,277
Stay down! I'm telling you
to stay down. Okay?! Stay down!

1135
01:44:42,736 --> 01:44:44,196
Get the cuffs on him.

1136
01:44:45,614 --> 01:44:47,324
- Call an ambulance!
- Keep still!

1137
01:44:47,574 --> 01:44:49,576
Call an ambulance!

1138
01:45:00,587 --> 01:45:02,089
Stay down!

1139
01:45:30,617 --> 01:45:33,078
Calm down! Calm down!

1140
01:45:33,328 --> 01:45:35,038
Nighttime! Nighttime!

1141
01:45:35,288 --> 01:45:36,915
You'll be home soon.

1142
01:46:03,650 --> 01:46:05,068
Hello, Michael.

1143
01:46:11,074 --> 01:46:12,909
I brought you a present.

1144
01:46:15,537 --> 01:46:19,875
I know you read an earlier draft.
But you gave me a better ending.

1145
01:46:21,877 --> 01:46:22,878
So, thank you.

1146
01:46:35,265 --> 01:46:37,768
Would you like me to tell you the plot?

1147
01:46:43,023 --> 01:46:44,941
It's about an American.

1148
01:46:46,234 --> 01:46:47,527
A blond.

1149
01:46:47,778 --> 01:46:49,404
A novelist.

1150
01:46:49,654 --> 01:46:52,657
People around her just keep dying.

1151
01:46:52,908 --> 01:46:54,493
But the question is:

1152
01:46:54,743 --> 01:46:56,286
Who's killing them?

1153
01:46:57,913 --> 01:47:02,542
Is the beautiful blond novelist
a serial killer?

1154
01:47:04,294 --> 01:47:06,546
Or is it the crooked cop?

1155
01:47:07,923 --> 01:47:09,549
Her analyst isn't sure.

1156
01:47:09,966 --> 01:47:13,386
But he goes crazy trying to find out.

1157
01:47:14,638 --> 01:47:16,723
But that's just half the story.

1158
01:47:16,973 --> 01:47:18,266
There's a twist.

1159
01:47:20,477 --> 01:47:25,315
You see, the novelist
never really killed anybody.

1160
01:47:25,565 --> 01:47:27,901
And neither did the cop.

1161
01:47:28,151 --> 01:47:31,154
The real killer all along...

1162
01:47:31,404 --> 01:47:33,115
was the shrink.

1163
01:47:49,005 --> 01:47:52,092
Yeah, from the moment he saw her...

1164
01:47:52,342 --> 01:47:56,680
he knew she was the smoke screen
he was looking for.

1165
01:48:00,600 --> 01:48:03,395
<i>His best opportunity to get even.</i>

1166
01:48:06,398 --> 01:48:07,524
First...

1167
01:48:08,775 --> 01:48:12,904
he'd deal with that scumbag
journalist.

1168
01:48:15,073 --> 01:48:19,244
<i>You see, you don't just go around
stealing another man's wife.</i>

1169
01:48:22,622 --> 01:48:24,040
It's humiliating.

1170
01:48:31,131 --> 01:48:34,092
Not that she was a complete innocent.

1171
01:48:34,342 --> 01:48:36,178
That weekend slut.

1172
01:48:38,430 --> 01:48:43,518
<i>Jesus, how could she
let that sleazebag touch her?</i>

1173
01:48:49,774 --> 01:48:51,067
It's hurtful.

1174
01:48:53,028 --> 01:48:56,281
And there's some hurts
you don't just get over.

1175
01:49:01,536 --> 01:49:02,787
Jealousy.

1176
01:49:06,833 --> 01:49:10,003
Jealousy can make us do crazy things.

1177
01:49:19,930 --> 01:49:21,973
But getting away with it...

1178
01:49:25,727 --> 01:49:27,854
that was genius.

1179
01:49:30,148 --> 01:49:32,651
<i>"Unfit to stand trial."</i>

1180
01:49:34,110 --> 01:49:37,113
No prison for him,
just a happy ending...

1181
01:49:37,530 --> 01:49:42,869
in a quiet, sunlit, peaceful
psychiatric institute.

1182
01:49:50,669 --> 01:49:54,589
Of course, that could all be a fiction.

1183
01:49:57,217 --> 01:49:59,803
He might really be insane.

1184
01:50:33,420 --> 01:50:35,255
Come back soon, baby.

1185
01:50:37,716 --> 01:50:39,259
I miss you.

